2. The Tricky Part

A brute-force approach is:

For every new price,

Keep moving left until a greater price is found.

Example

Prices

100 80 60 70 60 75
                ↑

For 75

Check

75 ≥ 60 ✓

75 ≥ 70 ✓

75 ≥ 60 ✓

75 < 80 ✗

Span

4

Doing this for every new price results in

O(n²)

Too slow.


---

3. Key Observation

Instead of checking previous prices every time,

Use a Monotonic Decreasing Stack.

The stack stores:

(price, span)

Whenever a new price is greater than or equal to the top price,

Pop it and add its span to the current span.

This way, each price is processed only once.


